Q1 = num_df.quantile(0.25)
Q3 = num_df.quantile(0.75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1

def iqr_outlier(k):
  outliers = ((num_df < (Q1 - k * IQR)) | (num_df > (Q3 + k * IQR))).sum()
  return outliers

import numpy as np 

def removeOutliers(x, outlierConstant):
  a = np.array(x)
  upper_quartile = np.percentile(a, 75)
  lower_quartile = np.percentile(a, 25)
  IQR = (upper_quartile - lower_quartile) * outlierConstant
  quartileSet = (lower_quartile - IQR, upper_quartile + IQR)
  resultList = []
  for y in a.tolist():
    if (y >= quartileSet[0] and y <= quartileSet[1]):
      resultList.append(y)
  return resultList


def detect_outlier(data_1):
  outliers = []
  threshold = -30
  threshold2 = 30
  mean_1 = np.mean(data_1)
  std_1 = np.std(data_1)
  for y in data_1:
    z_score = (y - mean_1) / std_1
    if (z_score < threshold or z_score > threshold2):
      outliers.append(y)
  return outliers

def inspect(var):
  if df[var].dtypes == "O":
    print("------------------------------PRINT ALL AND TYPE-----------------------------------")
    print(df[var])
    print("-------------------------------UNIQUE VALUES---------------------------------------")
    print(df[var].unique())
    print("-------------------------NUMBER OF MISSING VALUES----------------------------------")
    print(df[var].isna().sum())
    print("-------------------------PERCENT OF MISSING VALUES---------------------------------")
    print(df[var].isna().sum()/len(df[var]))
  elif df[var].dtypes == "float64":
    print("------------------------------PRINT ALL AND TYPE-----------------------------------")
    print(df[var])
    print("-------------------------------RANGE OF VALUES---------------------------------------")
    print("MIN", df[var].min())
    print("MAX", df[var].max())
    print("-------------------------NUMBER OF MISSING VALUES----------------------------------")
    print(df[var].isna().sum())
    print("-------------------------PERCENT OF MISSING VALUES---------------------------------")
    print(df[var].isna().sum()/len(df[var]))
